[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring native-image reflection issues**\n\nI’m considering the use of my own class for native images and how automatic reflection might work with `ConstructorTarget.class.getDeclaredConstructor`. It seems that the constructor needs to be available in metadata since it’s called from a library with variable types. This reflection may not be recognized as constant due to its location in `SecurityActions`. If the metadata is missing, it could fail with `NoSuchMethodException`. I wonder if direct queries in tests could help with auto-registration for native-image tests, even though it complicates things.\n\n**Considering reflection registration**\n\nI’m thinking about whether to use an assertion call, but that would involve a dynamic call in the test. Alternatively, I could annotate with `@RegisterReflectionForBinding`, though it isn’t in the dependencies. It's not strictly necessary, as native images can automatically detect and register fields. I can access the field with `MutableTarget.class.getField(\"value\")`, and using the `Field#set` method via `SecurityActions` should function properly. It’s a bit of a balancing act!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0dab34783e6bc6220169f11aaabf9c8192bb0b75a87ddc3645\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8RrJdXqUhFz4R_xmApceifFmChF8RhTxp4s2X7f7J6K9-mclAuMKTXo7xtwErC6QpRdkctTu025VER7AfLBq9iEFCBbtznEyeHMPZxRXM19mMPUZmnWeDJ4lDNlMZOmMVeetzjpwT3UE2mkNveCzuSHYVydwmJRdw0s-7ZO_ZOqRziIvaKHlcknGA_OsVZj5ayMDPyWXhm4kon5ddHfqXJahpOW_ONucPk2ft6afN5Uj6z0urCu3Sb5MYhV135FphPr4Qa7GoM1zAPvhFxzszsxM_UawKd0KKdMVr7er2WDw3yVfMnUXiivNBQJuusjEcT_-YrzUTnQHGgSocHf-aWk6kMtcWi_YiGzlhuh5matjum0z0f9CPt-u-e9c0vLOmadg1nMGYs8gECZ5J3zRSFN_mJOIpGGSw-wl3PQOPMv-XdtazbtUewJmYzDcAVNgHq3VDwxoCh7xlmxsleYs_O9xs6NZvm9M9h7abAlvpRp5iNEVYkcXCzukXZLuKCg0p5lj1pqUjN_i2wEZxVPZ3z3diCCn1OEIL4SPZQYAzScqBoQ5Q9RLJOru9ebHxrCkEvFKXKX3-aRn0isZdGTGTFyDg_qU